abstract: In “Bright, Infinite Future,” Mark Green assesses his political life and influence. “Gordon Bennett and the First Yacht Race Across the Atlantic” recounts the flamboyant publisher’s sailing experience.
snippet: In “Bright, Infinite Future,” Mark Green assesses his political life and influence. “Gordon Bennett and the First Yacht Race Across the Atlantic” recounts the flamboyant publisher’s sailing experience.
lead_paragraph: Mark Green, who was the city’s first public advocate, more or less admits that by 2009, the last time he sought elective office, New Yorkers were suffering from Green Fatigue.

abstract: Mr. Linton’s Drexel firm pioneered the junk bond industry and came to symbolize the era’s “greed is good” mentality, until it was swept into a federal inquiry.
snippet: Mr. Linton’s Drexel firm pioneered the junk bond industry and came to symbolize the era’s “greed is good” mentality, until it was swept into a federal inquiry.
lead_paragraph: Robert E. Linton, a prominent Wall Street executive who led the swashbuckling investment bank Drexel Burnham Lambert in the years before it imploded in scandal but who was largely untainted himself, died on Tuesday in Manhattan. He was 90.

abstract: More than a half-dozen prominent former national security officials support Apple in the debate over balancing privacy and security in the digital age.
snippet: More than a half-dozen prominent former national security officials support Apple in the debate over balancing privacy and security in the digital age.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In their years together as top national security officials, Michael V. Hayden and Michael Chertoff were fierce advocates of using the government’s spying powers to pry into sensitive intelligence data.

abstract: A charismatic point guard who achieved legend status as a Brooklyn schoolboy, he helped lift Syracuse University to national prominence in basketball and went on to play in the N.B.A.
snippet: A charismatic point guard who achieved legend status as a Brooklyn schoolboy, he helped lift Syracuse University to national prominence in basketball and went on to play in the N.B.A.
lead_paragraph: Dwayne Washington, better known as Pearl, a charismatic point guard who achieved legend status as a Brooklyn schoolboy before moving upstate, where he helped lift Syracuse University to national prominence in basketball, died on Wednesday in the Bronx. He was 52.

abstract: Left out of the Paris climate agreement, which is to be signed at the United Nations this week, the two industries nonetheless face pressure to be greener.
snippet: Left out of the Paris climate agreement, which is to be signed at the United Nations this week, the two industries nonetheless face pressure to be greener.
lead_paragraph: Even though commercial aviation and ocean shipping are significant sources of greenhouse gas emissions, they were excluded from the Paris climate treaty, to be signed by more than 100 countries this week at the United Nations in New York.

abstract: ‘The Amazing Max’ (Saturday and Sunday) Max Darwin, a.k.a. the Amazing Max, may come across like the M.C. at a raucous bar mitzvah party, but he does know his craft, and now he’s bringing it back to New York City for another round of shows. In this hourlong magic performance, he performs feats like mind reading, making objects disappear and then reappear, and sending coins raining from various parts of the body. The show includes lots of audience participation. (Through May 1.) At 3:30 p.m., Theater at Blessed Sacrament, 152 West 71st Street, Manhattan, 866-811-4111, theamazingmax.com.
